          "treatment": "Remove contaminated clothing. Decontaminate skin with soap and water. Atropine 1-3mg IV every 5-10 min until drying of secretions (target: HR >80, clear chest, dry skin). Massive doses may be needed (hundreds of mg). Pralidoxime 1-2g IV over 30 min, then 500mg/hr infusion (if within 24-48h of exposure). Benzodiazepines for seizures. Intubation and ventilation for respiratory failure."
